9:
Surely we can gather some info in a
town this big...
12:
That's true, but I think we've got a
bigger problem to worry about first.
19:
No way I'm getting through that, no
matter what we try to pull.
22:
Guess I'll just hang around here
while you guys go through.
26:
I should stay with him, just in case
anything happens. Go on—
29:
Pardon me, I couldn't help but
overhear your conversation. 
I think I might be able to lend a hand.
34:
Just your average merchant. Due to
the nature of my job, I know different
ways to get around these pesky
checks.
35:
For a suitable fee, you too can share
in this knowledge.
38:
Yeah? Guessing you got a few
secret routes for goods you don't
want inspected.
43:
All right, we'll take you up on that
offer.
46: Very good. If you'll follow me.
49:
You know the drill. No killing. We can
sell these folks off for a pretty penny.
52:
Good grief... I had hoped my
suspicions were unfounded.
54:
Hey, I'm still keeping my end of the
deal—you'll get into town...
59:
Heh... Pathetic fools. Very well! For
your ignorance, may you drown in
an ABYSSAL NIGHTMARE of your own
making!
74:
Whoa, Sotieth?! You didn't have to
do that! This was my idea, so I
should—
77:
Your objection is denied. It would be
troublesome if you are injured
before the plan is executed.
82:
Hey there, folks. What a day, huh?
Almost kidnapped by slavers!
88:
Tell me, is that woman behind you
the one controlling this Alter Device?
96:
Well, we shouldn't stick around
chatting here. You're trying to get
into town, right? Come with us.
99:
My comrades and I have a secret
entrance in. No inspections or
extortion money required.
102:
Your comrades? Just who in the
world are you?
105:
Ah, I skipped right over
introductions, didn't I?
109:
I'm Rashid, leader of the Golden
Dawn—a group that aims to free the
borderlands.
113:
I gotta say, I'm still blown away by
the fact that you recognized an Alter
Device.
116:
Well, we actually have a friend who's
got one too. Her name's Nephtim.
119:
Huh, very interesting. It'd be nice to
meet her someday!
123:
Not that I meant anything weird by
that! I'm just curious!
128:
Why are you directing that
comment to me? I did not say
anything.
133:
You said you found her in some
ruins, yeah?
136:
...Don't tell me you're planning on
using an ancient weapon like her to
start a war with the kingdom.
142:
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Sure, I rely on
Sotieth sometimes to fight, but I
swear that's not what we're trying to
do!
144:
The Golden Dawn's mission is to free
the borderlands—not pick a long
and bloody fight.
147:
...Not that the current situation
makes it look that way.
150:
Truth is, we're here to free people
from the borderlands who've been
enslaved.
154:
...You sure you should be telling us
that?
158:
I am, since I'm hoping you'll lend us
a hand.
160:
The kingdom's military might is
nothing to sneeze at. I'll take any
help we can get, especially if it's
someone who's already carved a
name for himself.
163:
Someone like... the Hellcat of the
Dunes.
167:
You're really gonna ask me, a guy
you barely know, to stick my neck
out and wrangle with those
kingdom assholes.
170:
Still, it wouldn't sit right with me to
turn away someone in need.
174:
There's also the matter of how you
intend to treat Sotieth—
178:
Th-those borderlands folks are
going crazy!
185:
The logical conclusion is that
someone acted early. There is a
high probability this will result in
large-scale riots and executions of
any captured parties.
190:
Are you serious? Guess we have no
choice but to put the plan into
action!
199:
You folks should come with! Once
the plan kicks off, it's gonna be hard
to get out of town!
204:
Oh, come on! I haven't even had a
pint yet!
209:
We're bringing the gate down!
Anyone who wants to keep their
head intact, stay back!
213: Stars, fall before me. Mut Nu!
216:
Rashid, everyone from the western
side has been freed! The other
sections should be coming soon too!
220:
Got it! Everyone, it's time to run as
fast as you can!
225:
Phew, I was worried for a bit there.
Looks like everything went well—
234:
Tch! Gonna call us scum, huh?
Should take a look in the mirror
yourself, punk.
239:
...Capture them all. Don't let a single
one escape!
244: Haridal! Why are you doing this?!
248:
Get it together, idiot! You can chat it
out later!
